			<div class="information-title">
				HTML Structures
			</div>
			<div class="information-description">
				<p>
					HTML structure is like a branching structure diagram. Elements encase other elements as if each element branches off into other elements.
				</p>
				<p>
					This is very difficult to put into words so please watch <a href="https://www.udacity.com/course/viewer#!/c-nd000/l-4137489485/e-2771378561/m-2771378562">This Video</a> for greater understanding on this topic.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="information" id="lesson2-3">
			<div class="information-title">
				Format and Boxes
			</div>
			<div class="information-description">
				<p>
					Every element on a webpage is enclosed in a box. Even if the image is a circle, it is enclosed in a box. The box can act as a border, which its size can be made customized and formatted.
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://www.udacity.com/course/viewer#!/c-nd000/l-4137489485/e-2608808598/m-2599508886">This video</a> does a good job in explaining it in more detail.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
